    {
      "p": "不仅…，更…",
      "e": "A climactic pair: 'not only A, but even more, B'. 更 upgrades the second clause above the first, stronger than plain 而且. 例：他不仅是老师，更是朋友。",
      "x": "语言不仅是交流的工具，更是思维的载体。 — Language is not merely a tool for communication; it is, even more, the vehicle of thought."
    },
    {
      "p": "并非",
      "e": "Formal, emphatic negation: 'by no means is / is not at all', typically correcting a likely misreading; 并 reinforces 非 (the literary 不是). 例：成功并非偶然。",
      "x": "这并非意味着语言是一座监狱。 — This by no means implies that language is a prison."
    },
    {
      "p": "与其说…，不如说…",
      "e": "'It is not so much A as B' — weighs two descriptions and declares the second more accurate. A staple of essay-style reflection. 例：与其说是运气，不如说是坚持。",
